01:54:28.310 --> 01:54:30.310
You can't. That's reality.

01:54:30.310 --> 01:54:32.310
You wanted a fairy tale, remember?

01:54:32.310 --> 01:54:34.310
No, I don't. I want to go home.

01:54:34.310 --> 01:54:40.990
Do a little more careful about what you wished for.

01:54:40.990 --> 01:55:00.400
Ha ha ha ha ha! Thanks, all.

01:55:00.400 --> 01:57:59.580
You did. It's my fairy tale.

01:57:59.580 --> 01:58:01.580
And if you can change it, so can I.

01:58:01.580 --> 01:58:03.580
Please, put that down!

01:58:03.580 --> 01:58:05.580
I'm going to put it down all right,

01:58:05.580 --> 01:58:23.930
and I'm going to close the book.

01:58:23.930 --> 01:58:30.990
Honey, what's the matter?

01:58:30.990 --> 01:58:32.990
It was all a dream.

01:58:32.990 --> 01:58:34.990
You were screaming. Are you okay?

01:58:34.990 --> 01:58:37.990
No, she's not. She's a nutcase.

01:58:37.990 --> 01:58:40.810
See?

01:58:40.810 --> 01:58:43.810
No, I'm fine.

01:58:43.810 --> 01:58:45.810
It was a stupid nightmare.

01:58:45.810 --> 01:58:47.810
I'm sorry.

01:58:47.810 --> 01:58:50.810
It's okay, honey. Go back to sleep.

01:58:50.810 --> 01:59:01.170
Guys, I know I've been kind of a pain.

01:59:01.170 --> 01:59:06.450
I think it's time to start giving up this fairy tale stuff.

01:59:06.450 --> 01:59:11.240
Hooray. That's fine, honey.

01:59:11.240 --> 01:59:14.240
Just don't give up on the kid inside altogether, okay?

01:59:14.240 --> 01:59:22.060
I'm never going to get back to sleep.

01:59:22.060 --> 02:00:12.030
Fairy tales again.

02:00:12.030 --> 02:00:16.030
If only she knew, she would have never gone back in that bed again.

02:00:16.030 --> 02:00:21.250
The end.

02:00:21.250 --> 02:00:27.400
So, don't take fairy tales lightly.

02:00:27.400 --> 02:00:30.400
You never know which ones are made up.

02:00:30.400 --> 02:00:33.400
And which ones are real.

02:00:33.400 --> 02:00:40.040
Excellent. I just have one question.

02:00:40.040 --> 02:00:43.960
What?

02:00:43.960 --> 02:00:46.960
Where's the part about the kids getting their heads chopped off?

02:02:47.000 --> 02:02:49.000
The Earthquake.

02:02:49.000 --> 02:02:51.000
Mutant Mole. What are you doing?

02:02:51.000 --> 02:02:53.000
I'm looking for breakfast, but it is so dark.

02:02:53.000 --> 02:02:57.000
You're in luck. My tasty Kellogg's Fruit Loops are in brighter colors.

02:02:57.000 --> 02:02:58.000
What's bright?

02:02:58.000 --> 02:03:01.000
Just follow my nose to the bright color of Kellogg's Fruit Loops.

02:03:01.000 --> 02:03:04.000
Now I see the shine of orange, lemon, cherry and lime.

02:03:04.000 --> 02:03:07.000
Fruit Loops. The bright part of this nutritious breakfast.

02:03:07.000 --> 02:03:08.000
Oh, they are bright.

02:03:08.000 --> 02:03:10.000
Dig in.

02:03:10.000 --> 02:03:11.000
Who turned out the lights?

02:03:11.000 --> 02:03:13.000
A few more will turn you on.

02:03:13.000 --> 02:03:15.000
Follow your nose to a most colorful fruit taste.

02:03:15.000 --> 02:03:28.280
Now, two can play the games of the Super NES Super Scope.

02:03:28.280 --> 02:03:32.280
Yoshi Safari and Metal Combat Falcon Revenge.

02:03:32.280 --> 02:03:43.160
So, to prepare yourself, you might want to consider some basic training exercises.

02:03:43.160 --> 02:03:45.160
Right here.

